OL,3,CTories pledge to make 'biological sex'
OL,4,Cprotected characteristic
OL,6,FThe Tories say that Labour's Equality
OL,7,FAct has not kept pace with evolving
OL,8,Finterpretations and is not
OL,9,Fsufficiently clear on when it means
OL,10,Fsex and when it means gender, and the
OL,11,Flaw needs to provide protections based
OL,12,Fon biological sex to enable rights to
OL,13,Fbe balanced fairly.
OL,15,FThe party says the proposed change to
OL,16,Fthe law will not remove the existing
OL,17,Fand continuing protections against
OL,18,Fdiscrimination on the basis of gender
OL,19,Freassignment provided by the Equality
OL,20,FAct.
